Juventus’ ambitious bid to sign Neymar from Paris Saint-Germain this summer fell short, Tuttosport reports. The Serie A champions were keen to sign the Brazilian, who would have partnered Cristiano Ronaldo in their attack and even offered Paulo Dybala plus €100million (£90m). Although Neymar was more interested in returning to Barcelona, PSG would rather have sold him to another European rival. However, Dybala was seemingly not keen on a move to Paris, choosing to remain in Turin. PSG also rejected Juve’s approach, as they were holding out for a larger up-front fee. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.